# --- Web3Forms Configuration ---
# Sign up at: https://web3forms.com/
# Get your access key from the dashboard
#
# ‚ö†Ô∏è CRITICAL SECURITY NOTICE FOR WEB3FORMS:
#
# 1. Web3Forms API keys are DESIGNED to be public (client-side usage)
# 2. The key WILL be visible in your production JavaScript bundle
# 3. This is NORMAL and EXPECTED behavior for client-side form services
# 4. Security is provided by Web3Forms domain restrictions, NOT key secrecy
#
# üîí REQUIRED SECURITY CONFIGURATION:
#
# You MUST configure these settings in your Web3Forms dashboard:
#
# ‚úÖ Domain Whitelist: Add ONLY your production domain(s)
#    Example: neuroforgetechnologies.net
#    DO NOT use wildcards unless absolutely necessary
#
# ‚úÖ Rate Limiting: Enable and configure appropriate limits
#    Recommended: 10 submissions per hour per IP
#
# ‚úÖ Email Notifications: Configure to receive submission alerts
#    This helps detect abuse or spam attempts
#
# ‚úÖ Spam Protection: Enable reCAPTCHA or hCaptcha if available
#    Additional layer of protection against automated abuse
#
# üìã DEPLOYMENT CHECKLIST:
#
# Before deploying to production:
# [ ] Web3Forms domain whitelist configured
# [ ] Rate limiting enabled in Web3Forms dashboard
# [ ] Email notifications configured
# [ ] Test form submission from production domain
# [ ] Verify form submissions are blocked from other domains
# [ ] Monitor submission logs for first 48 hours
#
# üö® WHAT IF MY KEY IS EXPOSED?
#
# If someone copies your Web3Forms key:
# - They CANNOT use it from other domains (if whitelist is configured)
# - They CANNOT bypass your rate limits
# - They CANNOT access your email or data
# - Web3Forms will reject submissions from unauthorized domains
#
# The key is like a public phone number - anyone can see it,
# but only authorized callers (domains) can get through.
#
# üìñ For detailed setup instructions, see: WEB3FORMS_SECURITY_SETUP.md
#
# VITE_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=your-access-key-here

