# ==============================================
# SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
# ==============================================
#
# 1. FILE SECURITY
#    ‚úÖ Add .env to .gitignore (already done)
#    ‚úÖ Only commit .env.example with placeholder values
#    ‚úÖ Never commit .env, .env.local, .env.production
#    ‚úÖ Use .env.example as a template only
#
# 2. ENVIRONMENT SEPARATION
#    ‚úÖ Use different values for each environment:
#       - Development: .env.development or .env.local
#       - Staging: .env.staging
#       - Production: .env.production
#    ‚úÖ Never use production secrets in development
#    ‚úÖ Never use development secrets in production
#
# 3. SECRET ROTATION
#    ‚úÖ Rotate API keys every 90 days
#    ‚úÖ Rotate passwords every 90 days
#    ‚úÖ Rotate tokens based on expiration policy
#    ‚úÖ Document rotation dates
#    ‚úÖ Use calendar reminders for rotation
#
# 4. ACCESS CONTROL
#    ‚úÖ Limit access to production secrets
#    ‚úÖ Use secret management tools:
#       - AWS Secrets Manager
#       - Azure Key Vault
#       - HashiCorp Vault
#       - Doppler
#    ‚úÖ Implement least privilege access
#    ‚úÖ Audit secret access regularly
#    ‚úÖ Revoke access when team members leave
#
# 5. SECRET MONITORING
#    ‚úÖ Use tools to detect exposed secrets:
#       - GitGuardian
#       - TruffleHog
#       - GitHub Secret Scanning
#    ‚úÖ Set up alerts for secret exposure
#    ‚úÖ Have an incident response plan
#    ‚úÖ Immediately rotate exposed secrets
#
# 6. CLIENT-SIDE EXPOSURE
#    ‚ö†Ô∏è  ALL VITE_ variables are PUBLIC
#    ‚ö†Ô∏è  Never put sensitive data in VITE_ variables
#    ‚ö†Ô∏è  Assume all VITE_ values are visible to attackers
#    ‚ö†Ô∏è  Use backend proxy for sensitive operations
#    ‚ö†Ô∏è  Validate all data server-side, never trust client
#
# 7. VALIDATION
#    ‚úÖ Validate all environment variables on startup
#    ‚úÖ Fail fast if required variables are missing
#    ‚úÖ Log configuration errors (without exposing secrets)
#    ‚úÖ Use TypeScript or validation libraries
#
# 8. DOCUMENTATION
#    ‚úÖ Document all environment variables
#    ‚úÖ Document which variables are required
#    ‚úÖ Document which variables are optional
#    ‚úÖ Document expected formats and values
#    ‚úÖ Keep documentation up to date
#
# 9. DEPLOYMENT
#    ‚úÖ Use platform-specific secret management:
#       - Vercel: Environment Variables in dashboard
#       - Netlify: Environment Variables in dashboard
#       - AWS: Systems Manager Parameter Store
#       - Docker: Docker Secrets
#    ‚úÖ Never hardcode secrets in deployment scripts
#    ‚úÖ Use CI/CD secret management features
#
# 10. BACKUP AND RECOVERY
#     ‚úÖ Keep secure backups of production secrets
#     ‚úÖ Store backups in encrypted format
#     ‚úÖ Document recovery procedures
#     ‚úÖ Test recovery procedures regularly
#
